						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the Kēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1445 Chitrabhānu, chaitra ba. 10,</hi> corresponding to 1522 A.D. April 21, Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is very much damaged except the portions containing date, name of the king and imprecatory passage.</p>						

